# Sero 1:1 engine — Cursor handover

You are picking up an in-flight engine. Read this whole file before editing.

## What this is

Sero is a **1:1 prep engine**: given a manager + a report + a meeting type, it
runs a pipeline that produces interview questions, drives the conversation, and
writes a post-meeting briefing. There is a CLI (`cli.js`) and a web frontend
(`frontend/`), but **the product is the engine in `src/`**.

This is **NOT a standalone app** — it is an engine meant to slot into a larger
system later. Bias every decision toward a clean, callable engine core.

**User's goal (do not drift from this):** improve the engine only — (1) clear arcs
for the 5 meeting types, (2) better prompts, (3) a great product. Not new features,
not the frontend, not infra.

## The 5 meeting types (arcs are good — leave them alone)

Registry: `src/one-on-one-types/` (`index.js` → `getType`, `listTypes`, `promptFor`).
Each Type owns `src/one-on-one-types/<slug>/type.js` with `tone_register`, `arc`,
`anti_patterns`, optional `eval_rules`, and a `prompts` set.

1. `bi-weekly` — Bi-weekly check-in
2. `performance` — Performance & feedback
3. `growth` — Growth & career plan
4. `feels-off` — Something feels off
5. `onboarding` — Onboarding check-in

`meeting-arcs.js` is a 9-line back-compat shim. `meeting-types.js` is just picker
copy (label/badge/duration/description).

## Pipeline stages (in order)

1. focus-points — `src/generate.js`
2. preparation — `src/preparation.js`
3. question-bank — `src/questions.js`, `src/question-generator.js`
4. questioning loop — `src/queue-manager.js` (675 lines, the biggest/most complex)
5. evaluation/briefing — `src/reviewer.js` + `src/briefing.js`

Shared prompts live in `prompts/`; the house set is wired in
`src/one-on-one-types/_shared/prompts.js`. A Type forks a prompt by setting its own
path in `type.js`; otherwise it inherits the shared one. Prompts use `{{PLACEHOLDER}}`
tokens filled by the stage runner before the API call.

