## Build / run / test

```bash
npm run dev      # api (frontend/server) + vite web, concurrently
npm run cli      # node cli.js — drive the engine from terminal
npm run smoke    # node scripts/smoke-test.js
npm run eval     # node scripts/eval.js — prompt notes + batch replay + briefing rules
```

Targeted regression tests in `scripts/` (run with `node scripts/<name>.js`):
`test-lexicon.js`, `test-opener-routing.js`, `test-drill-cap.js`,
`test-intro-order.js`, `test-prep-role-diff.js`, `manual-qa-verify.js`,
`batch-m5-verify.js`.

### Env / API keys

Create `.env` at repo root. Live model calls need `OPENAI_API_KEY` (lexicon review
can use `GEMINI_API_KEY`). Per-stage models are in `config/models.json`; override
per stage with `OPENAI_MODEL_{FOCUS_POINTS,PREPARATION,BANK,PLANNER,EVALUATION}` or
globally with `OPENAI_MODEL`. Offline tests above run without a key.

